	Innovation


Innovating education through partnerships


We recognise that the only way to keep pace with all the exciting opportunities in education is to challenge the traditional model of developing new ideas.  


In fact, at its core, it’s common sense. It’s about finding smart people - partners and customers inside and outside the company who can positively impact our business and learning outcomes.


Often that's about working with technology partners who can help us put education in the hands of more people around the world, in more inspiring ways. And it's about working with local experts, who know better than anyone what's needed to solve the challenges where they are.
Here are some examples of how we are doing that.


















Affordable learning

Low-cost private schools are an effective way to help drive up the quality of education for all students. 
Affordable learning










Parent Toolkit

We've contributed to a new toolkit to help parents understand their child’s journey from pre-kindergarten through high school.
Parent Toolkit










Build with Pearson

Pearson Developer gives developers access to our content and APIs so they can find innovative new ways to help people learn.
Pearson Developer






















